rComments: Prof. Cant is a great lecturer and passionate about the material he teaches. It was easy to follow along with his lectures. But the papers for this course were graded quite harshly and most students dropped the course half-way through the semester. The final exam was pretty tough as well, with extensive short answer questions and calculations.

A great prof. Very approachable and assignments are clear, precise and to the point. For a fourth year class the workload is quite reasonable, and he genuinely makes the effort to try and get you to enjoy and understand the material. He's not the easiest marker, but I never felt that I lost marks unfairly and he always provides good feedback.
Awful textbook... and his exam is ridiculously hard. The exam is based on both lectures and readings, so make sure to study both of them! But darn... he is so good looking.
